WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.280
Hello, dear friends! My name is Elena Proskura. I represent the company Moscow Business School,

00:10.280 --> 00:15.040
I am an active business coach and consultant in the field of personnel management.

00:15.040 --> 00:20.280
Today's topic is called Corporate Culture and Change in the Company.

00:20.280 --> 00:24.560
What tasks will be solved during this course?

00:25.160 --> 00:30.920
First of all, we would like to talk about corporate culture,

00:30.920 --> 00:38.440
to show the importance of the culture of the organization as a factor that can contribute to changes or interfere with them.

00:38.440 --> 00:42.640
We want to introduce you to the best practices of modern organizations

00:42.640 --> 00:47.400
that approach the reform, that is, the change of corporate culture,

00:47.400 --> 00:50.720
or individual subcultures or so-called microcultures.

00:50.720 --> 00:52.800
We want to present the experience of real projects,

00:52.800 --> 00:58.520
within which organizations reformed their culture and conducted an analysis of it,

00:58.520 --> 01:02.480
how it was done and what results they achieved.

01:02.480 --> 01:09.240
We want to introduce you to the tools that allow you to diagnose corporate culture,

01:09.240 --> 01:15.600
that is, from the analysis as it is to the further picture of the world or to the vision of how it will be,

01:15.600 --> 01:18.440
that is, to outline possible ways of its update.

01:18.480 --> 01:21.760
We want to show the role of political forces in the reform process,

01:21.760 --> 01:27.480
how political forces within the company influence the change of corporate culture,

01:27.480 --> 01:29.480
how they can contribute or interfere.

01:34.480 --> 01:38.480
Let's start with the corporate culture, its elements and functions.

01:38.480 --> 01:40.880
What is corporate culture?

01:40.880 --> 01:46.080
It is quite often said that it is corporate culture or organizational culture.

01:46.720 --> 01:50.720
Moreover, there are different approaches to understanding these two concepts.

01:50.720 --> 01:56.720
On the one hand, sometimes, speaking of corporate culture, it means organizational culture,

01:56.720 --> 02:02.320
and sometimes, under corporate culture, it means almost the same as organizational culture,

02:02.320 --> 02:04.320
only in relation to large corporations.

02:04.320 --> 02:10.720
Lately, more and more often, speaking of corporate culture, it means organizational culture.

02:11.360 --> 02:16.720
If we look deeper, including at dictionaries,

02:16.720 --> 02:25.080
the short encyclopedic dictionary of Bragaoza and Frona says that a corporation is a common name for many types of alliances

02:25.080 --> 02:30.080
that have an internal organization that unites members of alliances as one whole.

02:30.080 --> 02:34.080
It is a subject of rights and duties of a legal entity.

02:34.440 --> 02:41.440
The word culture in Vladimir Daly's dictionary means education, both moral and intellectual.

02:41.440 --> 02:47.440
The encyclopedia of sociology says that culture, from the Latin word for education,

02:47.440 --> 02:52.440
is a system of historical, developing and biological programs of human activity.

02:52.440 --> 02:54.440
I hope I did not confuse you.

02:54.440 --> 02:59.440
Let's get closer to what is happening now.

02:59.440 --> 03:03.440
What is corporate culture in the modern interpretation?

03:03.800 --> 03:08.800
Corporate culture is a system of material and spiritual values,

03:08.800 --> 03:11.800
manifestations that interact with each other,

03:11.800 --> 03:14.800
that are inherent in a corporation,

03:14.800 --> 03:20.800
that reflect its individuality and self-perception in the social and material environment,

03:20.800 --> 03:26.800
that manifest in behavior, interaction, self-perception and the environment.

03:27.160 --> 03:32.160
Quite often, when talking about corporate culture,

03:32.160 --> 03:39.160
it is said that it is a collection of rules, standards of behavior and ideological postulates

03:39.160 --> 03:43.160
based on the style of cooperation between employees, within the company,

03:43.160 --> 03:47.160
with clients and external counteragents.

03:47.160 --> 03:51.160
Let's do a little exercise.

03:51.520 --> 03:56.520
It is a joke, but through it you will be able to understand

03:56.520 --> 04:01.520
what corporate culture is and what its elements are,

04:01.520 --> 04:03.520
what its multifacetedness is.

04:03.520 --> 04:07.520
You need a clean sheet of paper and a pen for this.

04:08.520 --> 04:10.520
Have you taken it?

04:11.520 --> 04:13.520
Are you ready?

04:13.520 --> 04:19.520
Please write one animal and three qualities that you like it for.

04:19.880 --> 04:23.880
Write quickly, without thinking.

04:23.880 --> 04:25.880
The first thing that comes to your mind.

04:30.880 --> 04:32.880
Have you finished?

04:35.880 --> 04:39.880
Now write the second animal that you like too,

04:39.880 --> 04:42.880
and three qualities that you like it for.

04:42.880 --> 04:44.880
Write quickly, without thinking.

04:44.880 --> 04:46.880
The first thing that comes to your mind.

04:47.240 --> 04:51.240
If you have the same animal and the same definitions in the adjective,

04:51.240 --> 04:53.240
you can do it, it is not forbidden.

04:54.240 --> 04:56.240
Have you finished?

04:56.240 --> 05:00.240
Now write the third animal and three qualities that you like it for.

05:00.240 --> 05:02.240
Write quickly, without thinking.

05:03.240 --> 05:05.240
The conditions of the game are the same.

05:05.240 --> 05:07.240
If you have the same animal and the same qualities,

05:07.240 --> 05:11.240
you can write the same as the different variations.

05:11.240 --> 05:14.240
Other qualities are also animals and vice versa.

05:14.600 --> 05:16.600
Have you finished?

05:17.600 --> 05:19.600
Now do you want to know what it is?

05:20.600 --> 05:24.600
The first animal is what you want to be seen by.

05:25.600 --> 05:28.600
The second animal is what you are seen by.

05:28.600 --> 05:31.600
And the third animal is what you really are,

05:31.600 --> 05:34.600
or your subjective perception of yourself.

05:34.600 --> 05:38.600
This test is a joke, it is not a psycho-diagnostic, it is invalid,

05:38.600 --> 05:41.600
but in every joke there is a part of the truth.

05:41.960 --> 05:44.960
The same is true for corporate culture.

05:44.960 --> 05:46.960
In his book Corporate Religion,

05:46.960 --> 05:48.960
Jesper Kunde took the theory of Alfred Adler

05:48.960 --> 05:52.960
about the three-member perception of a person as a basis.

05:52.960 --> 05:58.960
He said that a company is perceived in three components as a person.

05:58.960 --> 06:00.960
The first component is the mission,

06:00.960 --> 06:03.960
how the company wants to be seen.

06:03.960 --> 06:05.960
The second component is the brand,

06:05.960 --> 06:07.960
how the company is seen.

06:08.320 --> 06:11.320
The third component is corporate religion,

06:11.320 --> 06:14.320
or the internal corporate culture of the company.

06:14.320 --> 06:17.320
The company as it is inside.

06:18.320 --> 06:21.320
What exists in it, what are the connections,

06:21.320 --> 06:23.320
what are the internal elements.

06:23.320 --> 06:26.320
In order to understand in general,

06:26.320 --> 06:29.320
we will talk about the components,

06:29.320 --> 06:32.320
about the elements of corporate culture.

06:32.320 --> 06:34.320
But before we move on,

06:34.320 --> 06:37.320
I want to say that in psychology there is a concept of congruence.

06:37.680 --> 06:40.680
One thing should correspond to another.

06:40.680 --> 06:42.680
That is, what we want to be seen

06:42.680 --> 06:44.680
should correspond to how we are seen

06:44.680 --> 06:46.680
and what we really are.

06:46.680 --> 06:48.680
If this does not happen,

06:48.680 --> 06:50.680
there is a kind of dissonance,

06:50.680 --> 06:52.680
there is no congruence.

06:52.680 --> 06:54.680
And the company is perceived

06:54.680 --> 06:56.680
not as a single whole, a single component.

06:56.680 --> 07:00.680
This directly affects the company's perception,

07:00.680 --> 07:02.680
its business results,

07:02.680 --> 07:04.680
and whether or not the consumer

07:04.680 --> 07:06.680
chooses the company.

07:07.040 --> 07:09.040
And this affects the employees

07:09.040 --> 07:11.040
who come to the company,

07:11.040 --> 07:13.040
and those who work in it.

07:13.040 --> 07:17.040
And this also affects the duration of the company's work.

07:17.040 --> 07:20.040
And this directly affects the changes.

07:20.040 --> 07:23.040
We'll talk about this a little later.

07:23.040 --> 07:25.040
Some time ago,

07:25.040 --> 07:28.040
the Association of Managers conducted a study.

07:28.040 --> 07:30.040
According to this study,

07:30.040 --> 07:33.040
the influence of corporate culture on something was determined.

07:33.040 --> 07:36.040
So what does corporate culture affect first of all?

07:36.400 --> 07:38.400
I mean not just corporate culture,

07:38.400 --> 07:40.400
but its presence.

07:40.400 --> 07:42.400
Because corporate culture is always there,

07:42.400 --> 07:44.400
even if it is not formalized.

07:44.400 --> 07:48.400
It is the conscious management of corporate culture

07:48.400 --> 07:51.400
and understanding of who we are.

07:52.400 --> 07:54.400
So, first of all,

07:54.400 --> 07:56.400
corporate culture affects the provision

07:56.400 --> 07:58.400
of a positive image of the company

07:58.400 --> 08:01.400
for the staff, shareholders and external audiences.

08:01.400 --> 08:04.400
When a company is perceived as a single whole,

08:04.760 --> 08:07.760
the image of the company is certainly increased

08:07.760 --> 08:09.760
in the eyes of the consumer,

08:09.760 --> 08:12.760
external agents and employees.

08:12.760 --> 08:14.760
And the degree of influence

08:14.760 --> 08:17.760
of a clearly formed corporate culture

08:17.760 --> 08:19.760
and a consciously managed one

08:19.760 --> 08:21.760
is quite high.

08:21.760 --> 08:23.760
It is high for the end result,

08:23.760 --> 08:25.760
for the business result.

08:27.760 --> 08:30.760
Next, what does corporate culture affect?

08:30.760 --> 08:32.760
It contributes to the achievement

08:33.120 --> 08:35.120
of the company's performance indicators.

08:35.120 --> 08:37.120
As I said,

08:37.120 --> 08:39.120
employees choose a company

08:39.120 --> 08:41.120
and become loyal to it

08:41.120 --> 08:43.120
based on the corporate culture

08:43.120 --> 08:45.120
that exists in the company.

08:45.120 --> 08:48.120
And the longer a person works in a company,

08:48.120 --> 08:50.120
the more effective he is.

08:50.120 --> 08:53.120
It is clear that more effective employees

08:53.120 --> 08:56.120
show and demonstrate much higher results

08:56.120 --> 08:58.120
than those who come

08:58.120 --> 09:00.120
and most of the people

09:00.120 --> 09:02.120
are in the company.

09:02.480 --> 09:05.480
For example, they are in the adaptation stage.

09:05.480 --> 09:07.480
The next factor

09:07.480 --> 09:09.480
that influences the corporate culture

09:09.480 --> 09:12.480
is that it contributes to the better motivation of the staff.

09:12.480 --> 09:15.480
The next one is one of the key factors

09:15.480 --> 09:18.480
in the strategy of the company's development.

09:18.480 --> 09:20.480
If our strategic goals are formed

09:20.480 --> 09:22.480
on the basis of the mission,

09:22.480 --> 09:24.480
and the mission is an integral part

09:24.480 --> 09:26.480
of the corporate culture,

09:26.480 --> 09:28.480
it is clear that we choose the strategy

09:28.480 --> 09:30.480
depending on our mission and values.

09:30.840 --> 09:32.840
The next factor

09:32.840 --> 09:34.840
that influences the corporate culture

09:34.840 --> 09:36.840
is that it contributes to the better performance

09:36.840 --> 09:38.840
of the business processes in the company.

09:38.840 --> 09:40.840
What is the corporate culture made of?

09:40.840 --> 09:42.840
What are its elements?

09:42.840 --> 09:45.840
The first one is the corporate mission declaration,

09:45.840 --> 09:47.840
corporate philosophy,

09:47.840 --> 09:49.840
corporate spirit,

09:49.840 --> 09:51.840
leadership style,

09:51.840 --> 09:53.840
corporate management,

09:53.840 --> 09:55.840
corporate management,

09:55.840 --> 09:57.840
corporate management,

09:57.840 --> 09:59.840
corporate management,

10:00.200 --> 10:02.200
corporate ethics,

10:02.200 --> 10:04.200
corporate image and reputation,

10:04.200 --> 10:06.200
human resources management,

10:06.200 --> 10:08.200
which is also an element

10:08.200 --> 10:10.200
of the corporate culture of the company,

10:10.200 --> 10:12.200
and quality control.

10:12.200 --> 10:14.200
How do we control the quality

10:14.200 --> 10:16.200
of our products, services,

10:16.200 --> 10:18.200
and goods?

10:18.200 --> 10:20.200
These are all the elements

10:20.200 --> 10:22.200
of the corporate culture.

10:22.200 --> 10:24.200
When we say that

10:24.200 --> 10:26.200
the corporate culture needs to be

10:26.200 --> 10:28.200
realized, formalized,

10:28.560 --> 10:30.560
and managed properly,

10:30.560 --> 10:32.560
we need to understand

10:32.560 --> 10:34.560
the functions of the company,

10:34.560 --> 10:36.560
what it carries.

10:36.560 --> 10:38.560
The main task is

10:38.560 --> 10:40.560
to create a common language.

10:40.560 --> 10:42.560
Often, the business owners

10:42.560 --> 10:44.560
and top managers

10:44.560 --> 10:46.560
use the term

10:46.560 --> 10:48.560
of a single cognitive apparatus.

10:48.560 --> 10:50.560
They say that we need

10:50.560 --> 10:52.560
our employees to speak the same language,

10:52.560 --> 10:54.560
to live in the same plane,

10:54.560 --> 10:56.560
in the same space.

10:56.920 --> 10:58.920
This is an objective reality.

10:58.920 --> 11:00.920
A huge number of mistakes

11:00.920 --> 11:02.920
are made by the company,

11:02.920 --> 11:04.920
including violations

11:04.920 --> 11:06.920
of internal business communications,

11:06.920 --> 11:08.920
as well as external business communications.

11:08.920 --> 11:10.920
That is why

11:10.920 --> 11:12.920
the creation of a single

11:12.920 --> 11:14.920
cognitive apparatus

11:14.920 --> 11:16.920
or common language

11:16.920 --> 11:18.920
is becoming more and more important.

11:18.920 --> 11:20.920
The employees of the company

11:20.920 --> 11:22.920
understand each other

11:22.920 --> 11:24.920
practically without words,

11:25.280 --> 11:27.280
and they are divided into categories

11:27.280 --> 11:29.280
of business purpose.

11:29.280 --> 11:31.280
The next function

11:31.280 --> 11:33.280
of the corporate culture

11:33.280 --> 11:35.280
is to create a boundary

11:35.280 --> 11:37.280
and a criterion for the other.

11:37.280 --> 11:39.280
When we talk about the corporate culture,

11:39.280 --> 11:41.280
we mean the mission

11:41.280 --> 11:43.280
and values.

11:43.280 --> 11:45.280
The only conflict

11:45.280 --> 11:47.280
that is not resolved

11:47.280 --> 11:49.280
is the conflict

11:49.280 --> 11:51.280
at the value level.

11:51.280 --> 11:53.280
That is why

11:53.640 --> 11:55.640
companies are increasingly

11:55.640 --> 11:57.640
addressing the values

11:57.640 --> 11:59.640
of the corporate culture

11:59.640 --> 12:01.640
and are forming

12:01.640 --> 12:03.640
the so-called corporate competencies.

12:03.640 --> 12:05.640
What are the corporate competencies?

12:05.640 --> 12:07.640
These are the personal features

12:07.640 --> 12:09.640
of people who correspond

12:09.640 --> 12:11.640
to the values of the company.

12:11.640 --> 12:13.640
When a company is selected,

12:13.640 --> 12:15.640
it starts to say that this person is its own,

12:15.640 --> 12:17.640
and this person is someone else's.

12:17.640 --> 12:19.640
Not everyone can fit into the company,

12:19.640 --> 12:21.640
not everyone can be effective in the company,

12:22.000 --> 12:24.000
and not everyone can be a good employee.

12:24.000 --> 12:26.000
The understanding of the values

12:26.000 --> 12:28.000
and philosophies

12:28.000 --> 12:30.000
of the company

12:30.000 --> 12:32.000
and its basic postulates

12:32.000 --> 12:34.000
leads to the fact

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
that the company understands

12:36.000 --> 12:38.000
who is its own, who is ours,

12:38.000 --> 12:40.000
and who is someone else's.

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
That is how

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
the corporate competencies are formed.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.000
The next function of the corporate culture

12:46.000 --> 12:48.000
is to motivate people

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
with values and to provide obedience.

12:50.360 --> 12:52.360
This is an important thing

12:52.360 --> 12:54.360
and it is also related

12:54.360 --> 12:56.360
to the ideology.

12:56.360 --> 12:58.360
Why is obedience important?

12:58.360 --> 13:00.360
Obedience to the staff

13:00.360 --> 13:02.360
and to the external consumers.

13:02.360 --> 13:04.360
The loyalty of the staff

13:04.360 --> 13:06.360
is important for the simple reason

13:06.360 --> 13:08.360
that a person becomes effective

13:08.360 --> 13:10.360
the second or third year of working in a company.

13:10.360 --> 13:12.360
The longer a person works,

13:12.360 --> 13:14.360
the more effective he is,

13:14.360 --> 13:16.360
because he knows the specifics,

13:16.360 --> 13:18.360
he knows the company,

13:18.720 --> 13:20.720
he knows the business goals.

13:20.720 --> 13:22.720
Of course, such employees

13:22.720 --> 13:24.720
are more effective and useful for the company.

13:24.720 --> 13:26.720
Moreover,

13:26.720 --> 13:28.720
if there is a process of change in the company,

13:28.720 --> 13:30.720
these employees are more loyal

13:30.720 --> 13:32.720
to the changes,

13:32.720 --> 13:34.720
because they live more

13:34.720 --> 13:36.720
with the interests of the company

13:36.720 --> 13:38.720
than only with their own.

13:38.720 --> 13:40.720
It is clear that

13:40.720 --> 13:42.720
it is difficult

13:42.720 --> 13:44.720
to expect

13:44.720 --> 13:46.720
that the employees

13:47.080 --> 13:49.080
will live only

13:49.080 --> 13:51.080
with the interests of the company.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.080
In order to do this,

13:53.080 --> 13:55.080
they need to be shareholders.

13:55.080 --> 13:57.080
However, if an employee is loyal

13:57.080 --> 13:59.080
to the company,

13:59.080 --> 14:01.080
he reacts more flexibly

14:01.080 --> 14:03.080
to the changes that may occur

14:03.080 --> 14:05.080
and he adapts

14:05.080 --> 14:07.080
to these changes better.

14:07.080 --> 14:09.080
He is ready to adapt

14:09.080 --> 14:11.080
because the company is

14:11.080 --> 14:13.080
his value level.

14:13.080 --> 14:15.080
The next function

14:15.440 --> 14:17.440
is the distribution of power,

14:17.440 --> 14:19.440
authority and status.

14:19.440 --> 14:21.440
It is the distribution

14:21.440 --> 14:23.440
of authority and status

14:23.440 --> 14:25.440
of the corporate culture

14:25.440 --> 14:27.440
and the style of management

14:27.440 --> 14:29.440
and internal business communication.

14:29.440 --> 14:31.440
The next function

14:31.440 --> 14:33.440
is the determination of the norms

14:33.440 --> 14:35.440
of behavior and relations.

14:35.440 --> 14:37.440
It is related to the corporate image

14:37.440 --> 14:39.440
and to the corporate management

14:39.440 --> 14:41.440
that tells

14:41.440 --> 14:43.440
how the company

14:43.800 --> 14:45.800
is formed in business

14:45.800 --> 14:47.800
and internal and external communication.

14:47.800 --> 14:49.800
The corporate standards

14:49.800 --> 14:51.800
are formed in various directions

14:51.800 --> 14:53.800
and they are formalized

14:53.800 --> 14:55.800
in the corporate code.

14:55.800 --> 14:57.800
We will talk about it later.

14:57.800 --> 14:59.800
Another function

14:59.800 --> 15:01.800
of the corporate culture

15:01.800 --> 15:03.800
is the formation of approaches

15:03.800 --> 15:05.800
to the work.

15:05.800 --> 15:07.800
How do we do it?

15:07.800 --> 15:09.800
What do we do?

15:09.800 --> 15:11.800
What don't we do?

15:12.160 --> 15:14.160
Now we will talk about

15:14.160 --> 15:16.160
each of the elements

15:16.160 --> 15:18.160
and the basic elements

15:18.160 --> 15:20.160
of the corporate culture.

15:20.160 --> 15:22.160
The important element

15:22.160 --> 15:24.160
of the corporate culture

15:24.160 --> 15:26.160
is the corporate spirit.

15:26.160 --> 15:28.160
It is often said

15:28.160 --> 15:30.160
that there is a corporate spirit

15:30.160 --> 15:32.160
in our company.

15:32.160 --> 15:34.160
It is often said

15:34.160 --> 15:36.160
that there is a microclimate

15:36.160 --> 15:38.160
in our company.

15:38.160 --> 15:40.160
What is the corporate spirit?

15:40.520 --> 15:42.520
The corporate spirit

15:42.520 --> 15:44.520
is defined as the following.

15:44.520 --> 15:46.520
The corporate spirit

15:46.520 --> 15:48.520
is the emotional and spiritual connections

15:48.520 --> 15:50.520
that are formed

15:50.520 --> 15:52.520
between the members of the team

15:52.520 --> 15:54.520
and they are formed

15:54.520 --> 15:56.520
around the mission

15:56.520 --> 15:58.520
and vision of the company.

15:58.520 --> 16:00.520
The psycho-emotional connections

16:00.520 --> 16:02.520
that are formed

16:02.520 --> 16:04.520
inside the company

16:04.520 --> 16:06.520
and the informal relations

16:06.520 --> 16:08.520
are the corporate spirit.

16:08.880 --> 16:10.880
Let's take a picture.

16:10.880 --> 16:12.880
There are two employees

16:12.880 --> 16:14.880
and in the distance

16:14.880 --> 16:16.880
they are crawling

16:16.880 --> 16:18.880
into something small

16:18.880 --> 16:20.880
and not very visible.

16:20.880 --> 16:22.880
One of them asks

16:22.880 --> 16:24.880
who is that?

16:24.880 --> 16:26.880
The other one answers

