I will not name the companies

01:22:39.160 --> 01:22:41.160
that used not very positive experiences

01:22:41.160 --> 01:22:43.160
in the same rebranding.

01:22:43.160 --> 01:22:45.160
When the company launched

01:22:45.160 --> 01:22:47.160
a new brand and did not

01:22:47.160 --> 01:22:49.160
provide any information

01:22:49.160 --> 01:22:51.160
about what will change in the company.

01:22:51.160 --> 01:22:53.160
At least, the answer to the question

01:22:53.160 --> 01:22:55.160
why you have become like this.

01:22:55.160 --> 01:22:57.160
One of the well-known companies

01:22:57.160 --> 01:22:59.160
that did rebranding

01:22:59.160 --> 01:23:01.160
went to the market with new brands

01:23:01.160 --> 01:23:03.160
when consumers asked

01:23:03.160 --> 01:23:05.160
why you changed your brand,

01:23:05.160 --> 01:23:07.160
what has changed.

01:23:07.160 --> 01:23:09.160
The employees were surprised

01:23:09.160 --> 01:23:11.160
to see the consumers

01:23:11.160 --> 01:23:13.160
and said that they did not know anything.

01:23:13.160 --> 01:23:15.160
What do you think?

01:23:15.160 --> 01:23:17.160
Did the company gain

01:23:17.160 --> 01:23:19.160
more respect and trust?

01:23:19.160 --> 01:23:21.160
It is unlikely.

01:23:21.160 --> 01:23:23.160
Even if the employees themselves

01:23:23.160 --> 01:23:25.160
do not know what is happening

01:23:25.160 --> 01:23:27.160
in their companies,

01:23:27.160 --> 01:23:29.160
they cannot clearly and argumentatively

01:23:29.160 --> 01:23:31.160
inform the consumer.

01:23:31.160 --> 01:23:33.160
It is clear that the consumer

01:23:33.160 --> 01:23:35.160
does not know what is going on.

01:23:35.160 --> 01:23:37.160
Maybe there is a crash,

01:23:37.160 --> 01:23:39.160
maybe we will have problems.

01:23:39.160 --> 01:23:41.160
We better vote by foot

01:23:41.160 --> 01:23:43.160
and go to another company.

01:23:43.160 --> 01:23:45.160
This is how the influence

01:23:45.160 --> 01:23:47.160
of management of changes in the company

01:23:47.160 --> 01:23:49.160
influences.

01:23:49.160 --> 01:23:51.160
In particular, at the stage of rebranding.

01:23:51.160 --> 01:23:53.160
The situation with the influence

01:23:53.160 --> 01:23:55.160
of absorption.

01:23:55.160 --> 01:23:57.160
There are situations

01:23:57.160 --> 01:23:59.160
when companies merge

01:23:59.160 --> 01:24:01.160
and absorb.

01:24:01.160 --> 01:24:03.160
There is no clear understanding

01:24:03.160 --> 01:24:05.160
of how the corporate culture

01:24:05.160 --> 01:24:07.160
will change.

01:24:07.160 --> 01:24:09.160
And there is a surge of shaking.

01:24:09.160 --> 01:24:11.160
The company can go through

01:24:11.160 --> 01:24:13.160
a long period of process

01:24:13.160 --> 01:24:15.160
of merging and absorption.

01:24:15.160 --> 01:24:17.160
If there is a separate

01:24:17.160 --> 01:24:19.160
structural division in the company,

01:24:19.160 --> 01:24:21.160
at the stage of merging and absorption,

01:24:21.160 --> 01:24:23.160
when this process is going on,

01:24:23.160 --> 01:24:25.160
they begin to form their corporate culture.

01:24:25.160 --> 01:24:27.160
And a subculture.

01:24:27.160 --> 01:24:29.160
Then this subculture

01:24:29.160 --> 01:24:31.160
can show up

01:24:31.160 --> 01:24:33.160
as a slow-moving mine.

01:24:33.160 --> 01:24:35.160
This is a risk that

01:24:35.160 --> 01:24:37.160
can be avoided with a deliberate

01:24:37.160 --> 01:24:39.160
and conscious management.

01:24:39.160 --> 01:24:41.160
What are the paradoxes

01:24:41.160 --> 01:24:43.160
of information transformation changes?

01:24:43.160 --> 01:24:45.160
Surprisingly, the older and more stable

01:24:45.160 --> 01:24:47.160
the organization, the more difficult

01:24:47.160 --> 01:24:49.160
it is to start a process of change.

01:24:49.160 --> 01:24:51.160
This is a predictable paradox.

01:24:51.160 --> 01:24:53.160
The older the company,

01:24:53.160 --> 01:24:55.160
the more established

01:24:55.160 --> 01:24:57.160
the norms, rules and standards.

01:24:57.160 --> 01:24:59.160
Even if they are not formalized.

01:24:59.160 --> 01:25:01.160
Imagine a bureaucratic machine

01:25:01.160 --> 01:25:03.160
that used to live by its standards

01:25:03.160 --> 01:25:05.160
in the Soviet Union.

01:25:05.160 --> 01:25:07.160
Most of the staff

01:25:07.160 --> 01:25:09.160
has been working

01:25:09.160 --> 01:25:11.160
for 20-40 years.

01:25:11.160 --> 01:25:13.160
Suddenly, young managers

01:25:13.160 --> 01:25:15.160
come and try to implement

01:25:15.160 --> 01:25:17.160
some Western standards.

01:25:17.160 --> 01:25:19.160
There was a tough machine

01:25:19.160 --> 01:25:21.160
that had subordination,

01:25:21.160 --> 01:25:23.160
bureaucratic standards.

01:25:23.160 --> 01:25:25.160
And suddenly,

01:25:25.160 --> 01:25:27.160
new things appear.

01:25:27.160 --> 01:25:29.160
It is clear that

01:25:29.160 --> 01:25:31.160
the existing environment,

01:25:31.160 --> 01:25:33.160
the conservative environment,

01:25:33.160 --> 01:25:35.160
will actively resist

01:25:35.160 --> 01:25:37.160
these changes.

01:25:37.160 --> 01:25:39.160
This is what happens in government structures

01:25:39.160 --> 01:25:41.160
where new managers

01:25:41.160 --> 01:25:43.160
and new formations

01:25:43.160 --> 01:25:45.160
come in and the staff

01:25:45.160 --> 01:25:47.160
starts to growl and actively resist.

01:25:49.160 --> 01:25:51.160
Unfortunately,

01:25:51.160 --> 01:25:53.160
this is what happens.

01:25:53.160 --> 01:25:55.160
Some staff leaves

01:25:55.160 --> 01:25:57.160
because of these changes

01:25:57.160 --> 01:25:59.160
or because they don't understand

01:25:59.160 --> 01:26:01.160
the benefits of these changes.

01:26:01.160 --> 01:26:03.160
Sometimes we lose important people

01:26:03.160 --> 01:26:05.160
that we can't find on the market.

01:26:05.160 --> 01:26:07.160
Or we part with those people

01:26:07.160 --> 01:26:09.160
who stop the process of change

01:26:09.160 --> 01:26:11.160
and prevent the company

01:26:11.160 --> 01:26:13.160
from moving forward.

01:26:15.160 --> 01:26:17.160
What else is a paradox?

01:26:17.160 --> 01:26:19.160
A manager who hired a new employee

01:26:19.160 --> 01:26:21.160
who has a corporate culture

01:26:21.160 --> 01:26:23.160
and is more progressive

01:26:23.160 --> 01:26:25.160
should balance

01:26:25.160 --> 01:26:27.160
two things.

01:26:27.160 --> 01:26:29.160
He should balance

01:26:29.160 --> 01:26:31.160
the basic values of the existing company

01:26:31.160 --> 01:26:33.160
and its values

01:26:33.160 --> 01:26:35.160
and competencies

01:26:35.160 --> 01:26:37.160
that are a bit ahead

01:26:37.160 --> 01:26:39.160
of the competencies

01:26:39.160 --> 01:26:41.160
of the existing employees.

01:26:41.160 --> 01:26:43.160
This should be taken into account.

